  <summary date="2019-06-19T04:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Expanding Access to Graduate Education Act of 2019

This bill allows income-eligible graduate students who received Pell Grants during their undergraduate education to utilize their remaining Pell Grant eligibility toward their first graduate degree, subject to the existing 12-semester duration limit. Currently, Pell Grants are available only to undergraduate students.</summary>
